The fiasco at the opening match of the World Cup in Ahmedabad raises many important and serious questions. 

When the sale of tickets went live on BookMyShow ahead of the tournament, the tickets were  "sold off" within minutes. Then, how is it possible that just a few hundred people turned up for the match? 

Newspaper reports suggest that 40,000 tickets were offered free of cost to women for the match by the BJP to celebrate the passage of the Women's Reservation Bill. From where did these 40k tickets come? Can BCCI allot tickets to a political party in this manner? 

Interestingly, the Women's Reservation Bill was passed in the last week of September but the ticket sales was over by first week of September. Then, from where did these extra tickets come for women? 

It shows that there is a nexus that operates which has kept the cricket fans in the dark for long. There is no transparency in the ticketing process which leads to disillusionment for countless fans. 

Even after free tickets and snack coupons, women did not turn up for the match. They were even misled that it's a India-Pakistan match to fill the stadium. But, women did not turn up. 

Here is a thing for BCCI, let cricket be a gentleman's game as it is called. Chuck out the politics or one day you will see cricket in peril.
